<br>
Zyce, very good points, but a pet class with J Boots would give you a terrible time.  A mage for example with damage shields on himself and pet running away while the pet beats on you would hurt bad.  A Wizard with J Boots needs only a second to shadow step and nuke you with spells you have a hard time resisting from who knows where.  Necros are a different game, they can't snare you, but their life tap and leach spells you can't resist.  So if they can get a few of them off they can win.  Add in a pet and I think that tips the scales.  Even more so if the necro is post 50 and has the high level rogue pet.  You fight pet or run to caster and get back stabbed.  Enchanters are in trouble, every thing they have, except the pet is based on MR.  If they can get away from you and force you to fight there pet, they may have a shot, other wise they are in trouble. <p>Eryl Flynn Level 51 Wood Elf Minstrel on Prexus
